block content

  +state(name, path, 'The Great Lake State', 'January 26, 1837')

  .intro
    p The current Michigan flag is the third version for the state. Descriptions of the first two flags exist, but their specific designs have been lost to history.
    p The first Michigan flag was notable in its depiction of Governor Stevens T. Mason. He is the only real person besides George Washington to appear on a state flag.
    p Michigan’s flag now follows the common pattern of a field of blue charged with the state coat of arms.
    p This version was officially adopted June 26, 1911.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Michigan flag features a field of blue charged with the state coat of arms, centered.
      +survey(name, '59th')
    .visual.flag
      +flag(name, path)

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-elk-moose.svg', alt='an elk and a mooose face each other on hind legs, their front legs on a shield')
          h4 elk & moose
          p natural beauty, regional fauna
          p #[em Note:] The elk and moose are said to be borrowed from the Hudson’s Bay Company coat of arms.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-eagle.svg', alt='eagle with laurel and arrows in its claws')
          h4 eagle
          p freedom, peace, strength, the Union
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-man.svg', alt='a man holds a gun and waves on the shore')
          h4 armed man
          p peace, strong defense
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-tuebor.svg', alt='Tuebor')
          h4 motto
          p #[em I will defend]
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-e-pluribus-unum.svg', alt='E Pluribus Unum on a banner')
          h4 motto
          p national unity, #[em Out of many, one]
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan-icon-motto.svg', alt='Latin words on a banner')
          h4 motto
          p #[em If You Seek a Pleasant Peninsula, Look About You]

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p Established in 1835, the Michigan coat of arms bears resemblance to the coat of arms of the #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hudson%27s_Bay_Company#/media/File:HBC-coa.JPG') Hudson’s Bay Company], which also features an elk and moose as supports.
    .visual.flag
      +coat-of-arms(name, path)

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Only azure and white (argent) are specifically mentioned in the statute for the coat of arms. No colors are specified for the flag.
