  .guide
    .content
      h2 Construction
      p Michigan statute doesn’t specify dimensions for its flag. It is usually produced with a proportion of 2:3.
    .visual
      +construction(name, path)

  .guide.wide.timeline
    .content
      h2 Previous iterations
      ul.visual.flag-list
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.blank(src='/assets/images/blank.jpg', alt='a blank rectangle')
          h4 1837–1865
          p Lost to time, but as described: The first flag featured the coat of arms plus a woman and soldier. The reverse featured a portrait of Stevens T. Mason.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.blank(src='/assets/images/blank.jpg', alt='a blank rectangle')
          h4 1837–1911
          p Lost to time, but as described: The woman and soldier were removed from the obverse. Mason’s portrait was removed and the U.S. coat of arms was added to the reverse.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.blank(src='/assets/images/flag-michigan.svg', alt='the current flag of Michigan')
          h4 1911–Present
          p The U.S. coat of arms were removed from the reverse.
        li.flag-item

